Depandencies:

this is used to downloed the depandencies for the appliction from the onther chart 

Eg:

consider you are deplying an e-commars application which reqires MySQL, nginx, redis etc.. 

in general , we will create a chart for e-commars and another chart for MySQL, nginx, Redis.

and we will install each depandencies saperaatly and then we will install our appliction chart again. so wich will consule more tiime and energy, so to avoid that, we will creat an directory called as "chert" inside the ecommars chart and pass all the dependencies in that and then we will install an single chart 


Instead of creating these from scratch, you reuse existing Helm charts.

this is the existing helm chart 


My Application
       │
       ├── MySQL Chart
       ├── Redis Chart
       └── Rabis chart


here, we will pass this complet chart  in chart.yaml file  of the main chart , that is as below


ecommerce/

Chart.yaml
values.yaml
templates/


inside the chart.yaml  we will pass the dependencies as below


Example:

chart.yaml

apiVersion: v2
name: ecommerce
description: Helm chart for an ecommerce application
type: application
version: 0.1.0
appVersion: "1.0"

dependencies:
  - name: mysql
    version: "13.4.2"
    repository: "https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami"

  - name: redis
    version: "20.0.0"
    repository: "https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami"


